snippet.textDisplay: Absolutely brilliant and pristine rendition both in terms of lyrics and music. Coke studio's experiment to modernize Pakistan's musical scene, while keeping original tones intact is incredible. This is big plus of Pakistan's coke studio, infact it is a case study to understand that we dont need to rape our classical music through RAP songs culture.  I would really suggest that for next season Coke studio should think of collaborating with some Indian musicians i.e AR Rahman, Amit trevedi etc to give new dimensions to subcontinent's music. It will be historic to witness that talent from both countries is working under one roof for the betterment of our common heritage... All the best.. Much Love to motherland Pakistan from Dublin...
